Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
is in  Singapore  for medical checkups after an eye operation, the
state-controlled Sunday Mail said.  Mugabe recently had cataract procedures while on holidays
in Singapore, the Harare-based newspaper reported, citing
presidential spokesman George Charamba. Mugabe is set to return
before his 87th birthday on Feb. 21, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Nelson Gore Banya in
